00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,600
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:07,664
[Episode Thirty-four]

3
00:00:16,283 --> 00:00:18,958
[Li Dazhao, styled Shouchang, Director of Peking University Library]

4
00:01:24,077 --> 00:01:27,234
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Professor at Peking University]

5
00:01:52,642 --> 00:01:54,969
[Chen Yannian, eldest son of Chen Duxiu]

6
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:20,000
"Laboratory and Prison"

7
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,880
There are two locations where civilization in the world began.

8
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,880
The first is a scientific laboratory.

9
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,200
The second is prison.

10
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,120
Our youth aspire that

11
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,880
if it's not the laboratory where they are, then it should be the prison.

12
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,520
And it works the other way too.

13
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,440
This is the most noble and beautiful way of life.

14
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:42,960
Civilization born in these two places is the true civilization.

15
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:47,200
It is a civilization that is both alive and valuable.

16
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,040
Fellow citizens,

17
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:13,280
now everyone in this country has stood up.

18
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,160
Just yesterday

19
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:19,840
in Shanghai and Tianjin

20
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,440
students went on a general strike,

21
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,280
workers went on a general strike,

22
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,280
businesses went on a general strike.

23
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,720
Many firms in Shanghai have also made their voices heared that

24
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:32,720
they are willing to stop their business to save the arrested students,

25
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,520
and they swear not to reopen the market until those traitors are punished.

26
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:36,960
Right now,

27
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,200
petition groups organized by Beijing Federation of Students

28
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,440
have arrived at the Presidential Palace.

29
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,160
We have put forward three demands.

30
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:47,520
First, punish the traitors.

31
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:51,200
Second, do not sign the peace treaty.

32
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:52,480
Third,

33
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:55,680
we will never recognize Hu Renyuan as the President of Peking University.

34
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,360
We pledge that

35
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,480
we will never leave until the government fulfills all three demands.

36
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:05,520
Good!

37
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,760
No mercy towards the traitors!

38
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:10,400
Give me back Qingdao and my freedom!

39
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,160
Punish the traitors!

40
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,880
Give me back Qingdao and my freedom!

41
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,640
Down with the traitors

42
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,600
Cao Rulin, Zhang Zongxiang, Lu Zongyu!

43
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,440
Down with the traitors

44
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:25,040
Cao Rulin, Zhang Zongxiang, Lu Zongyu!

45
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:28,400
The way Beiyang government brutally suppressed

46
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,560
the students' patriotic movement

47
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:33,280
aroused great indignation among the people.

48
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,520
From the beginning of June,

49
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:38,480
tens of thousands of teachers and students from dozens of schools in Beijing

50
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,920
took to the streets

51
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:42,960
holding large-scale demonstrations and speeches.

52
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:46,240
Workers, merchants

53
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,000
and people from different classes,

54
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:50,480
all went on strikes

55
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,560
to support the student movement.

56
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:57,760
In Shanghai, Tianjin, Jinan, Wuhan, Guangzhou and other places,

57
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,680
there were also massive eruptions

58
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:02,400
as people went on strike together.

59
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,440
The May Fourth Movement spread rapidly,

60
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,840
like volcanoes

61
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:11,040
bursting all over the country.

62
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,841
[Fu Yuefen, Acting Minister of Education]

63
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,000
Premier Qian has arrived.

64
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,120
Thank you for waiting.

65
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,560
We are on the edge now.

66
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,720
The President has some unfinished business.

67
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,920
He had me come here first.

68
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:30,880
Have a seat.

69
00:06:33,736 --> 00:06:35,170
[Qian Nengxun, styled Xicheng, Premier of the Beiyang Government]

70
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:34,880
Things have changed.

71
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,480
Both of you know the situation in Beijing.

72
00:06:35,884 --> 00:06:37,370
[Wu Bingxiang, Chief of Metropolitan Police]

73
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,360
I will skip that.

74
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,560
Let's talk about Shanghai first.

75
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,320
This afternoon, in Shanghai,

76
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:42,240
people went on strike as schools, markets and labour are all involoved.

77
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:44,800
The community in Shanghai held a joint meeting

78
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,080
at Kalden West Hotel, Ningbo Road.

79
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,320
They founded Shanghai Federation of Business, Students,

80
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,360
Industry and Newspapers.

81
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,640
They sent a telegram to the whole country,

82
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,720
declaring that one more day the traitors remain unpunished,

83
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,720
one more day this strike will keep going on

84
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,920
at all costs.

85
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:56,880
Other than Shanghai,

86
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,640
more than a dozen cities across the country,

87
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:01,040
also in Paris and Tokyo,

88
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,320
there have been large-scale

89
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,440
protests against the government.

90
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:04,720
Today only,

91
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,080
the Presidential Palace and State Council

92
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,760
has received more than 300 protest telegrams.

93
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,120
This is unprecedented.

94
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:10,240
More importantly,

95
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,240
the southern government is using this situation

96
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,520
to win over people's hearts,

97
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,040
attacking this government aggressively.

98
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,040
Even some foreign banks and trading companies

99
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,880
have asked us to keep the situation under control as soon as possible,

100
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,400
so to protect the interests of foreign businessmen.

101
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:23,040
The education community in Beijing is completely out of control now.

102
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,440
Whatever advantages we had previously,

103
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:26,880
we lost them all.

104
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,360
Almost every schools are on the streets today.

105
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,840
There was a workers' parade in Changxindian.

106
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,160
With workers involved this can really go out of control.

107
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,640
It is on the edge right now.

108
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,200
The President, General Duan and I just now

109
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:40,320
had an urgent meeting.

110
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:43,200
It is imperative that we can control the situation.

111
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,840
We have to win over students' hearts at all costs.

112
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,840
Is there a way to do this considering what we have done?

113
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,440
There are ways.

114
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,680
That's why you two are here now.

115
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,800
But,

116
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,000
it all comes to you two to do this.

117
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:55,520
Please instruct us.

118
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:56,800
Duan Shuai said that

119
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,880
as we are in the middle of negotiation with the southern government now,

120
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,480
considering that the southern government is using

121
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,000
this mess caused by students

122
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:03,200
as an excuse to attack us.

123
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,720
We can't lose big over an insignificant matter like this.

124
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,960
We can't lose to them and to the people at the same time.

125
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:10,000
So, by all means, we have to keep things in Beijing under control.

126
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,480
So, what, Duan is giving in?

127
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,480
That's not like him.

128
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,080
It's not giving in.

129
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,320
It's strategy, tactics.

130
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,160
Cut the nonsense.

131
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,000
What's the trick? Come on.

132
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,320
By presidential decree,

133
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,400
Wang Huaiqing is removed from his duty as the Army Chief.

134
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,160
Duan Zhigui is removed from his duty as Commander.

135
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,560
All infantry, soldiers and others shall be evacuated.

136
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,240
Public security in Beijing

137
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,760
will be handed over to the Metropolitan Police Department.

138
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:37,840
Signed, Xu Shichang.

139
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:40,480
This is us taking a step back.

140
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,840
I see.

141
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,320
So that's why it's only me here today.

142
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,000
Turns out those two are let go

143
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,760
just in these few days.

144
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,160
Wait.

145
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,320
Without the troops, how can I manage all those students

146
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,600
only using the police force?

147
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,400
Director Wu, if you have any complaints,

148
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,200
please send it to your master Duan Qirui.

149
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:04,880
I'm just here to convey the order.

150
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,800
If you still want to come to the meeting tomorrow,

151
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,000
just go and do your job.

152
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,520
I'm not complaining.

153
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:10,960
I just want to know,

154
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,800
with the troops withdrawn, the gendarmerie withdrawn,

155
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,800
what good can us police do?

156
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,000
Maintain order.

157
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,240
Wait for the order to evacuate.

158
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,000
Fine, fine.

159
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,280
Minister Fu,

160
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,920
you are to consult with the principals of each school as soon as possible

161
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,360
on the aftermath of police evacuation.

162
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:32,720
The government has only one condition.

163
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,480
Students are to resume classes immediately.

164
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,560
As soon as the arrested students are released,

165
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,320
I will be on it.

166
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,160
But the government has to promise that

167
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,160
the military police must not meddle with the students affair again.

168
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:43,920
The students affair only gets more complicated

169
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,400
when the police got involved.

170
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,480
Do you think I really care for this shitshow?

171
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,080
Your lack of management is why

172
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:52,880
a bunch of scholars can push the students into causing trouble.

173
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,240
If it weren't for that,

174
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,440
my life would be a lot easier.

175
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,480
Enough!

176
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,160
Does arguing work?

177
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,000
Director Wu,

178
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,440
you need to convey

179
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,480
the dismissal order of those two.

180
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:11,440
Very well.

181
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,600
Wait a second.

182
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:16,240
This is your job. Why should I go?

183
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:18,560
This is the instruction from General Duan and the President.

184
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,080
Weigh that yourself.

185
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,760
Fine, I'm going.

186
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:27,760
Director Wu, I am leaving to work too.

187
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,160
Decree of the President of the Republic of China.

188
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,000
First, all arrested students

189
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,800
are released immediately.

190
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,280
Second, police will retreat unconditionally.

191
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:54,640
All personnel will withdraw from along the Beiheyan Avenue and the Horse God Temple.

192
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:58,560
Third, the Ministry of Education will be responsible for public security.

193
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:02,000
Xu Shichang, President of the Republic of China.

194
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:03,200
Open the door.

195
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,440
What's going on?

196
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,640
Students, students.

197
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,400
You must calm down.

198
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,360
Come out and talk to us if you have something to say.

199
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,280
After collective discussion, all our students

200
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,440
determined to never leave prison!

201
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:50,560
Never leave prison!

202
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:51,798
Classmates!

203
00:11:51,798 --> 00:11:53,280
Classmates, please be quiet!

204
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,600
Here is a telegram from the Beijing Student Union.

205
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,000
It's sent to the whole country.

206
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,000
I am here to read it out.

207
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,640
The government has made a fool of itself.

208
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:05,920
Students are detained for no reason,

209
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,520
and cannot leave by themselves.

210
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,480
The military police ravaged schools, undermined justice,

211
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:12,560
violated human rights, abandoned their humanity.

212
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:14,880
If this is tolerated, how can we serve the country?

213
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,880
Serve the country! Never leave prison!

214
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,440
Serve the country! Never leave prison!

215
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,200
Tell me what you want,

216
00:12:23,680 --> 00:12:25,200
so that the students can come out.

217
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,480
Please be more specific.

218
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:29,440
I'll go back and ask my superiors for instructions.

219
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,800
Dismiss the traitors

220
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:32,560
Zhang Zongxiang, Cao Rulin, Lu Zongyu.

221
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,400
Okay, okay, no problem.

222
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:37,200
I'll ask my superiors for instructions right away.

223
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,200
Yes, victory is in sight.

224
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,560
Hang in there. Yeah!

225
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,280
Come on, come on!

226
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:42,080
Come on!

227
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:44,480
Come on!

228
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,560
Now students' demands are

229
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,760
the removal of

230
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,800
Cao Rulin,

231
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:51,920
Zhang Zongxiang,

232
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,120
Lu Zongyu.

233
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,640
This is also their bottom line.

234
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:57,680
Otherwise, it will be difficult to convince them.

235
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:59,920
Students push their luck.

236
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,240
Explain that there must be someone behind them.

237
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,360
Let's talk about it. What should we do?

238
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:07,840
I'll speak first.

239
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,760
I have received today

240
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,600
four telegrams from Chief Lu from Paris.

241
00:13:11,685 --> 00:13:14,026
[Xu Shichang, pen name Juren, President of the Republic of China]

242
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:12,800
He said that

243
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,400
the residence of the Chinese delegation in Paris

244
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:15,520
has been surrounded,

245
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,200
and the local Chinese have suggested

246
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:19,120
that if the government can detain patriotic students,

247
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,240
then they can follow that example

248
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,360
and detain Chinese envoys.

249
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:23,280
If we don't release the students,

250
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,560
the delegation

251
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,920
will be likely treated as traitors

252
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,920
and attacked by the local Chinese.

253
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,200
I studied the students' demands carefully.

254
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:34,640
They're not really high.

255
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,360
After all, the Paris Peace Treaty was not brought out.

256
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,560
In the end,

257
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,960
it's nothing more than to remove Cao, Zhang, and Lu

258
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,640
and give the nation a chance to express its anger.

259
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,480
I think we can't lose this big event

260
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:49,680
because of these few people.

261
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,600
It's time to make up your mind.

262
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,600
If we continue to delay,

263
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,200
the students will make other demands.

264
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:56,400
That would be troublesome.

265
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,520
I agree with Premier Qian's opinion.

266
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,440
I agree with Premier Qian's opinion.

267
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,360
I agree with Premier Qian's opinion.

268
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,040
I agree. I agree.

269
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,920
I also agree with the Premier's opinion.

270
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,560
Director Wu, what's your opinion?

271
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:16,880
At this point,

272
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,240
what else can I say?

273
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,320
I'll just carry out your decision.

