00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:24,880
Good. Director Wu's attitude is very good.

275
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:28,560
Now everyone is in agreement.

276
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,280
I also discussed this matter with Old Duan.

277
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:32,400
Now it's here again.

278
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,640
It's really time to get past this hurdle.

279
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:36,560
I have to condescend to

280
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,080
Cao Rulin and the others first.

281
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:42,160
So please ask Acting Minister Fu

282
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,320
to formally apologize to the students on my behalf.

283
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:47,040
At the same time, a formal order will be issued to remove

284
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,360
Cao, Zhang, and Lu from their positions.

285
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,040
Yes.

286
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:53,200
Presidential decree.

287
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:58,640
Cao Rulin, Zhang Zongxiang, and Lu Zongyu are dismissed.

288
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,520
Cao Rulin has also resigned from his position

289
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,520
as manager of the Bank of Communications.

290
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,280
escaping to Xiaotangshan.

291
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,040
Xu Shichang.

292
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,000
Long live Chinese academia!

293
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,760
Long live Chinese academia!

294
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,520
Long live Chinese academia!

295
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,280
Long live Chinese academia!

296
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,480
We won!

297
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:48,480
Gentlemen,

298
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,000
originally,

299
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,560
I thought Peking University was going to die this time. Really.

300
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:55,120
But I didn't expect it to come back to life.

301
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,000
Therefore, everything

302
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,040
requires you to persist

303
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,680
and persist in your efforts.

304
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,560
I'm not as optimistic as you.

305
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,720
Now it's just a staged victory.

306
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,480
Master Cai hasn't come back yet.

307
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,960
There will be more torment at the back.

308
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:13,200
And the Paris Peace Treaty is still to be considered.

309
00:16:13,205 --> 00:16:16,001
[Lu Xun, Civil servant under the Ministry of Education]

310
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,680
That matter is not resolved.

311
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,880
It will never stop.

312
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,440
Fortunately, there is already hope.

313
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:22,240
Mr. Lu Xun,

314
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,320
what spark of thought do you have?

315
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,440
Come and let us hear.

316
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,880
What have I seen this month?

317
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,160
Thanks to brother Zhongfu,

318
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:33,440
the backbone of China,

319
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,200
the enlightenment effect of the New Culture Movement

320
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,400
has already appeared.

321
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,720
The lions of East Asia are awakening.

322
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,960
So what's next?

323
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,280
Destroying the submissiveness

324
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,960
in our national character

325
00:16:44,316 --> 00:16:46,002
[Hu Shi, styled Shizhi, Professor at Peking University]

326
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,480
and turning it around.

327
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,680
Then let's pursue the victory.

328
00:16:46,924 --> 00:16:49,194
[Gao Yihan, Professor at Peking University]

329
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,520
Urge the government to refuse to sign the Paris Peace Treaty

330
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,040
and not give up until we reach our goal.

331
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,240
I have a different point of view.

332
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:58,080
Modern society pays attention to their respective duties.

333
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,240
We are a school.

334
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:02,480
Peking University is the highest institution of higher learning in China.

335
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,320
We have to do something that we should do

336
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,200
at Peking University,

337
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:07,040
and it's not easy for us to get over this hurdle.

338
00:17:05,517 --> 00:17:07,089
[Liu Bannong, Professor at Peking University]

339
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:09,040
We should now focus on

340
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:10,880
how to restore order to our school

341
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:12,720
as soon as possible.

342
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:14,640
The first priority is to quickly return to class.

343
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:18,320
Mr. Shizhi, which is the most important priority for Peking University:

344
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,320
patriotism or attending classes?

345
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,880
Patriotism is not contradictory to class attendance.

346
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:25,200
So can you save the country without class?

347
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,320
We are a school.

348
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,800
Patriotic and national salvation is a long-term solution.

349
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,800
Attending class is a daily matter.

350
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,440
The importance of the priority is self-evident.

351
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,640
This is a rare reunion in such a crisis.

352
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:40,880
Let's talk about our "New Youth"

353
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:41,760
and the "Weekly Review".

354
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:43,600
What's the next step?

355
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,520
I have an idea.

356
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:48,560
For more than three years, we at "New Youth"

357
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,680
have been enlightening people's minds.

358
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:52,800
Now,

359
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,200
people have begun to wake up.

360
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,960
After the awakening,

361
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,480
what should we do?

362
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:01,440
I wonder if you have ever thought about this question.

363
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,160
The most realistic thing now is to boycott the Paris Peace Treaty.

364
00:18:02,558 --> 00:18:05,508
[Qian Xuantong, styled Deqian, Professor at Peking University]

365
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:06,160
Get Qingdao back.

366
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,480
You can't win if you don't take the risk.

367
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,280
Right.

368
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:10,560
Deqian,

369
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,160
after boycotting the Paris Peace Treaty

370
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:13,840
if a country's

371
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,280
problem is not solved at all,

372
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,480
similar problems will also

373
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:17,760
come out one by one.

374
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:21,200
It is also empty talk to strengthen the country and enrich the people.

375
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,560
What's wrong now

376
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:23,920
is this rotten regime.

377
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:25,440
Then my point is clear.

378
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:28,560
Fight, we must fight to the end.

379
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,440
I still have the same old argument.

380
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:33,360
I don't advocate violent revolution.

381
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,640
I don't advocate talking about socialism all the time.

382
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,240
We should be practical.

383
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,160
Speaking of learning from foreign countries,

384
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,960
my opinion is to learn from the United States.

385
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,320
Everyone, don't forget,

386
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,360
our New Culture Movement,

387
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,440
our banner is science and democracy.

388
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:49,040
So China must learn from the United States

389
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:51,040
in all aspects to develop.

390
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:58,400
Deqian,

391
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,800
didn't you tell me the other day,

392
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:03,120
that you think Shizhi has some foreign worship?

393
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,320
Why don't you talk about it?

394
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:07,760
So-called democracy is to express one's own opinion.

395
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,120
Don't hide it.

396
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,960
I wanted to publish it.

397
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,040
But I really haven't organized it yet.

398
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:16,560
Shizhi.

399
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:19,440
Worshiping foreign things, not ingratiating myself.

400
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,280
Not ingratiating yourself?

401
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,280
Excuse me, Dr. Hu,

402
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:24,400
these days

403
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:25,680
you follow Professor Dewey's ass

404
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,600
with a bag in your hand every day

405
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,480
like a sidekick. Isn't that flattering?

406
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:33,120
Shizhi, I know a person who is particularly like you.

407
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,160
Who?

408
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:38,560
That old queue beside Gu Hongming, Liu Er.

409
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,800
Yes or no?

410
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:43,680
Bannong, I say this because

411
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,400
I think we can all express our own opinions.

412
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:49,280
However, we express our views in order to find the direction.

413
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:52,400
As for the different views and familiarity,

414
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:56,000
it is different depending on the country and the times.

415
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:58,000
A gentleman's harmony is different.

416
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:01,280
This harmony is what we have in common now.

417
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,360
What do we have in common?

418
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:06,240
I think that is no matter what,

419
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:09,280
we should transform the current society.

420
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,680
It is a transformation, not an improvement.

421
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:13,600
It's a revolution.

422
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:16,560
This is because I have come to a conclusion

423
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,960
after seeing all the perverse practices

424
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:21,120
of the Beiyang government.

425
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,960
And I want to tell you,

426
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:26,240
since we have launched such a campaign

427
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,080
at this critical moment,

428
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,720
we should stand up bravely

429
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,520
and act directly.

430
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:35,600
This is also the responsibility of those of us

431
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:38,800
who are awakened in the present.

432
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:45,280
I have no dress, I share it with my fellows.

433
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,520
I will work with you.

434
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:52,080
I count myself in.

435
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:56,560
Shouchang,

436
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:58,160
I have a worry.

437
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,520
What?

438
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:02,000
Worried about the split of our "New Youth".

439
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:06,400
Now we quarrel almost as soon as we meet.

440
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:08,640
I know what you mean.

441
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:12,560
Shizhi has too much faith about the United States.

442
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:15,120
Too much faith in Dewey's experimentalism.

443
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,560
Actually, he doesn't think about it.

444
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:18,320
How can China's feudal system for thousands of years

445
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:21,120
be changed by talking and writing?

446
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,440
If there is no big revolution,

447
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,760
China can't catch up with the world trend.

448
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,400
I used to think that you two

449
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,240
are too radical.

450
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,320
Shizhi? He's too moderate.

451
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,520
I choose between you two.

452
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,000
But now I think

453
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,280
I have more inclinations.

454
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:44,560
This is bound to make Shizhi feel more isolated.

455
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:46,800
Shouchang, let me remind you,

456
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,720
Shizhi is very respectful.

457
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,440
Don't be too hard on him on some occasions.

458
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:54,160
There are some things I tell him about,

459
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:55,520
and he can barely get by.

460
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:58,720
You talk too much, it's hard for his face.

461
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,040
You can rest assured,

462
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:02,880
I didn't treat him as an outsider.

463
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:07,440
What do you mean by inclination just now?

464
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,280
About Marxism.

465
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,600
A while ago, I was compiling the manuscript

466
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,120
of the next issue of "New Youth".

467
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:15,200
I put the long article you wrote

468
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:16,960
"My View of Marxism"

469
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,720
and read it again carefully.

470
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,680
At the same time, on 6 April

471
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,120
I published in the "Weekly Review"

472
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,720
second chapter of the "Communist Manifesto",

473
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,120
"Proletarians and Communists".

474
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:28,640
I also read it carefully.

475
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,840
It was very touching and I felt a lot.

476
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,840
You said in the editor's note

477
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,360
of the "Communist Manifesto"

478
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,800
that this is Marx's and Engels's

479
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:39,120
first and foremost opinion.

480
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:42,160
This is a great inspiration to me.

481
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:45,680
Shouchang, I think you are now

482
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:48,000
the first person in China

483
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,680
to advocate and believe in Marxism.

484
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:52,320
So I need to ask you something.

485
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:53,760
Don't be afraid to ask for advice.

486
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,000
Actually, when I was in Japan,

487
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,240
I've been paying attention to Marxist theory.

488
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,200
I'm writing now

489
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,320
the second half of

490
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,040
"My View of Marxism".

491
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,120
But I really want to know

492
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:06,080
your views and opinions on the first half.

493
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,800
At least now I think

494
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:11,280
Marxism is more reasonable

495
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,120
than anarchism.

496
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,760
It is more rational than Dewey's experimentalism.

497
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:18,160
But as to whether it is

498
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,000
the most advanced theoretical system of our time,

499
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,120
it's hard to say.

500
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,640
Because I didn't read

501
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,200
all of Marx's works.

502
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:27,920
In fact, I have been concerned

503
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:29,760
about Marxist theory for many years.

504
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:33,040
I found out when I was in Japan before.

505
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:35,200
There are many people studying Marx's

506
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:36,880
socialist theory in Japan

507
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:38,400
and translated a lot of materials.

508
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,720
Originally, I just read its principles.

509
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:43,200
Such as historical materialism,

510
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,640
dialectical materialism,

511
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:47,840
socialism from utopian to scientific.

512
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,680
But recently,

513
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,920
I will combine it with the reality of China to read it.

514
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:54,720
The more I read, the more I feel open.

515
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:57,280
Brother Zhongfu, I have an idea,

516
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:58,960
if China wants to develop

517
00:23:59,360 --> 00:24:01,200
we must rely on Marxist theory

518
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,720
to be our guiding ideology.

519
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,360
Besides, it's hard to find a second way.

520
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:09,280
Are you so sure of your conclusion?

521
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:11,360
This is just my preliminary idea.

522
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,360
But after the May Fourth Movement,

523
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,080
my belief is getting stronger and stronger.

524
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:20,080
Of course, it also needs to be demonstrated and considered.

525
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:21,840
So what do you think

526
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:23,600
about the Russian October Revolution?

527
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:26,720
This question,

528
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,240
I have published before

529
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:29,680
in the "Comparative View of French-Russian Revolutions"

530
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:30,720
and explained it.

531
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:32,560
In general,

532
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,480
the Russian October Revolution

533
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,720
is completely different from the British and French revolutions.

534
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,280
I think it is the most advanced revolution.

535
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:40,720
How do you say this?

536
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:43,360
In the final analysis, the British and French revolutions of the past

537
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,520
are also bourgeois revolutions.

538
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,600
But the October Revolution in Russia was different.

539
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,840
It is a proletarian-led

540
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:51,200
socialist revolution.

541
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:52,800
According to Marxist theory,

542
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:54,640
socialist revolution

543
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:57,360
is the inevitable result of the development of capitalism.

544
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,280
In this sense,

545
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,120
it must be the most progressive revolution.

546
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:03,200
I don't read many books of Marx.

547
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:04,480
But I know

548
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:07,040
a basic viewpoint of socialist theory

549
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:10,000
is that socialist revolution breaks out

550
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:13,360
only after capitalism

551
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,480
has fully developed.

552
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,160
But now Russia

553
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,400
is not a developed capitalist country.

554
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:20,560
I didn't know this at first.

555
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:23,120
But then I read Lenin's book

556
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:24,320
and I realized.

557
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:25,680
Lenin has a point of view

558
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:27,360
that socialist revolution

559
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:29,200
can break out and succeed

560
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:31,040
in the weaknesses

561
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:32,480
of imperialism.

562
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:34,480
Look at the Russian October Revolution.

563
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,320
It's been almost two years now.

564
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,520
The Soviet government

565
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,240
is surrounded by layers of imperialism

566
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:41,920
and has gained a firm foothold.

567
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,560
This is enough to illustrate that Lenin's point of view

568
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:45,760
is correct.

569
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:46,880
So you're saying

570
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,920
a poor and weak country like China

571
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:52,480
can also have a socialist revolution?

572
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:54,080
I'm still studying this point.

573
00:25:54,640 --> 00:25:56,000
However, the October Revolution in Russia

574
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:58,000
has set an example for us.

575
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:00,800
Well, Shouchang,

576
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,320
you taught me a lesson today.

577
00:26:13,360 --> 00:26:13,840
Junman!

578
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:15,520
You're back!

579
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:16,320
Dad.

580
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:17,040
What are you doing here?

581
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:18,080
I'm taking her out.

582
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:19,600
Sir.

583
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:20,880
We'll have dinner soon.

584
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:22,000
Add a few more dishes.

585
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:24,000
I'm going to invite Shouchang and Shizhi to dinner tonight.

586
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:25,200
Okay.

587
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:34,720
Smells good.

588
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:36,560
Sister-in-law.

589
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:37,280
Here. Here.

590
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:39,200
I'm eating Anhui cuisine again.

591
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:41,840
Strictly speaking, this is not Anhui cuisine.

592
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:44,400
Anhui cuisine refers to Huizhou cuisine.

593
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:46,160
This should be Wan cuisine

594
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,360
or Anqing cuisine.

595
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:48,480
Then enjoy your meal.

596
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:49,920
I will take the children out to dinner.

597
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:51,040
Thanks, sister-in-law.

598
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:51,600
Don't mention it.

599
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:53,280
Here comes the wine. Hello, gentlemen.

600
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,000
This is General Zou Yongcheng's

601
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:58,160
two jars of old wine brought to me by my client.

602
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:00,880
He said they've been staying there for a long time.

603
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:02,880
Today, we will open them.

604
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:03,360
Great.

605
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:04,240
Brother Shouchang,

606
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:05,840
I'm willing to come to Zhongfu for dinner.

607
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,120
Look at so many good dishes.

608
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,960
Old wine has also been brought out for us.

609
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,120
When I was as old as Yannian,

610
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,320
I already had a lot of children.

611
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:15,600
Yannian has the Six No's, no drinking.

612
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,120
I won't force him.

613
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,440
But I ask him to pour wine for the two uncles.

614
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,240
It's my respect for you both.

615
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,320
Brother Zhongfu, what are you doing?

616
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:25,200
No, no.

617
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:25,840
It's nothing.

618
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,400
The students were released.

619
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:32,480
Cao Rulin, Zhang Zongxiang, Lu Zongyu,

620
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,480
I'm glad they're all dismissed.

621
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,400
I want to drink some wine.

622
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,760
Come on, gentlemen.

623
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,400
Let me propose a toast to you first.

624
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,520
Cheers.

625
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:46,720
Good.

626
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:56,720
Henian.

627
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,080
Time to eat.

628
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,240
Time to eat, Henian.

629
00:28:03,910 --> 00:28:05,773
[Chen Qiaonian, second son of Chen Duxiu]

630
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,600
Mom, they are eating fish.

631
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,400
We have meat. Meat is better than fish.

632
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:13,040
Here, Mom will give you a piece of meat.

633
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,040
Why can't I go?

634
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,400
It's too personal.

635
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:17,120
When you're eighteen next year,

636
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,320
you can go to the table.

637
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:21,040
The old man is also the leader of the New Culture Movement,

638
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:23,360
engaging in these feudal ethical codes at home.

639
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:24,320
I protest.

640
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:25,200
I also protest.

641
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,440
Why don't you let me be with Yannian?

642
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:29,520
I also protest against the feudalism of the old man.

643
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:30,480
Keep your voice down.

644
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:31,920
Why are you so rude?

645
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:33,280
Eat some meat.

646
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,560
Stop protesting, go and eat meat.

647
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,440
Delicious?

648
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:42,000
You all know.

649
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:45,760
I was in shock the other day.

650
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,240
Sort of

651
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,320
experienced a transformation.

652
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,960
Brother Zhongfu, don't worry too much.

653
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:54,720
It's all in the past.

654
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:55,840
Now isn't our Peking University

655
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:56,960
Peking University again?

656
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:00,800
Is Peking University the original Peking University?

657
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:01,680
I don't know.

658
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:02,720
I, Chen Duxiu,

659
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:04,320
am not the original Chen Duxiu anymore.

660
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,560
This is an article I wrote yesterday.

661
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:11,680
Yannian.

662
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:14,800
Read it to the two uncles.

663
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,360
"Beijing Citizen Manifesto"

664
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:22,400
The Chinese nation is a nation that loves peace.

665
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:25,520
Today, despite the unbearable internal and external oppression,

666
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:26,960
we still put forward

667
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:29,600
the final minimum demands for the government.

668
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:31,840
First, regarding diplomacy towards Japan,

669
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:34,480
we must not abandon the economic rights of Shandong Province

670
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:38,240
and must cancel two secret agreements in four years and seven years of the Republic of China.

671
00:29:38,880 --> 00:29:41,520
Second, expel Xu Shuzheng, Cao Rulin

672
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:43,680
Lu Zongyu, Zhang Zongxiang, Duan Zhigui

673
00:29:43,760 --> 00:29:44,880
Wang Huaiqing and others

674
00:29:45,280 --> 00:29:46,640
from Beijing.

675
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,840
Third, dismiss the Nine Gates Infantry Commander

676
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,680
and the garrison commander.

677
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:54,960
Fourth, the Beijing security troops will be organized by citizens.

678
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:57,120
Five, citizens must have

679
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,960
absolute freedom of assembly and speech.

680
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:01,760
I still hope that the people can achieve this goal by peaceful means.

681
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,600
The government is still unwilling to make peace

682
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,680
and completely disobeys the wishes of the citizens.

683
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,920
We, students, businessmen, laborers,

684
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,760
soldiers and others have no choice but to take direct action

685
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:11,440
to make fundamental changes.

686
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:12,560
We hereby declare

687
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:14,880
that we sincerely hope that people at home and abroad will understand our declaration.

688
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:20,080
Brother Zhongfu, what does this mean?

689
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:22,560
This is what I'm talking about.

690
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,800
We should stand up bravely.

691
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,840
I have three points to explain.

692
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:31,120
First, I totally agree with Shouchang.

693
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,920
Expand the student movement into

694
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:36,800
social movements and mass movements.

695
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:40,720
Second, make our demands clear for the next step.

696
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:42,960
Third, publicly declare

697
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:45,600
that if the government doesn't respect public opinion,

698
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,280
we will take direct action

699
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:51,120
in order to realize the fundamental transformation of society.

700
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:52,960
And today?

701
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,400
I just want to ask the opinions of you three.

702
00:30:57,280 --> 00:31:00,640
And I also want Shizhi to translate it into English.

703
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,800
Brother Zhongfu, that's great.

704
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,760
Mobilize the public to publish widely.

705
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:10,320
Yannian, you print more.

706
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,320
Give it to me after printing, and I'll distribute it myself.

707
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,040
Okay.

708
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,320
Brother Shouchang,

709
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:16,480
you are an open young professor of Peking University

710
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:18,240
handing out leaflets on the street.

711
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:19,840
What a scandal!

712
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:22,320
No, Shizhi.

713
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,600
I've never thought of myself

714
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,040
as superior to others.

715
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:30,240
Look, for the national interest,

716
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,560
people can go to the streets, workers can go to the streets,

717
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,080
women can go to the streets.

718
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,600
What can't I do on the streets?

719
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:38,880
Don't you tell people about equality and freedom every day?

720
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,800
How come I can't do it here?

721
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,240
Shizhi, I think you are

722
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,560
a new culture on the outside

723
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,640
but an old morality on the inside.

724
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,560
It's not the same on the inside.

725
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:53,360
Shouchang, I've always respected you.

726
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,200
An iron man in culture.

727
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,120
But I really don't understand.

728
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,360
You and brother Zhongfu

729
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,280
are all men of culture.

730
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,280
What are we going to talk about?

731
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:04,960
A man of culture is a scholar.

732
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,480
The scholar is concerned

733
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,560
with the cultivation of the body, the family, the country and the world

734
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:12,000
to have a sense of family and country, to cultivate Qi and maintain peace.

735
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,800
Now we have been doing self-cultivation.

736
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,440
Family. Is our family all together?

737
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:18,720
The two of you have come a long way

738
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,160
from poverty to now.

739
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:21,440
And now?

740
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:24,080
A Lu Bu among men, a red hare (=ideal horse) among horses.

741
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:25,920
But why do you have to ruin your future?

742
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:27,760
Even at the expense of your wife and children?

743
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:29,520
I really don't know what you are doing.

744
00:32:32,223 --> 00:32:33,115
Shizhi.

745
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,400
Actually, that's a good question.

746
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,840
Now let me answer you.

747
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:41,760
I don't think people can live for themselves.

748
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:44,640
Go to Changxindian

749
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,560
and look at those dilapidated sheds.

750
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:48,800
Go to Jinpu Railway Line and see

751
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:50,080
the thousands of miles of hungry refugees.

752
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:51,840
Go to Qianmen Avenue again

753
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,760
and look at those beggars begging along the street.

754
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:55,840
Shouldn't we do something for them?

755
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,160
Do you expect us to be like you?

756
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,520
Clean and shiny?

757
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:04,000
Mr. Dazhao.

758
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:05,600
I think what you said is excellent.

759
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:08,400
The country should throw caution to the wind at this point.

760
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:11,440
Give up the few, to save the many.

761
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,120
You can't have it both ways.

762
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:16,080
Yannian, do you have anything to say?

763
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,040
Brother Zhongfu, it's fine.

764
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:21,120
Yannian can express his opinion.

765
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,920
Sorry, Uncle Hu.

766
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:28,720
Shizhi,

767
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,360
I was a little harsh just now.

768
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:32,880
Sorry.

769
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:34,080
Not a problem.

770
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:36,640
It really doesn't matter.

771
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:38,560
I know you are an open-minded person.

772
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,120
Sit down, gentlemen.

773
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,200
You all know I like to debate.

774
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:44,960
Only by debating can the truth come out.

775
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,440
Let's raise our glasses.

776
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,240
Here.

777
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:05,280
Shizhi. Shizhi.

778
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,440
No, this isn't like you.

779
00:34:07,600 --> 00:34:09,520
You don't have to hide it.

780
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,280
Tell me what you think.

781
00:34:12,640 --> 00:34:14,000
I'm not hiding anything.

782
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,120
I think

783
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:16,960
brother Zhongfu wanting to make this civic declaration

784
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,400
is unnecessary.

785
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:21,760
Besides, Mr. Dewey has just arrived in China,

786
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:23,280
just entered Beijing.

787
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:26,000
So every day I'm busy arranging

788
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,200
the speech for him.

789
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,680
I need to talk to the Ministry of Education about all these things

790
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,360
and some government departments

791
00:34:31,680 --> 00:34:33,120
and ask them to come forward and arrange these things in person.

792
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:35,600
I don't want to make these relationships too rigid.

793
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,440
Mobilize the citizens for democracy. I agree.

794
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:41,520
I also agree with the five points mentioned,

795
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:42,720
especially the fifth one.

796
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,720
But what it says here,

797
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:47,840
"We, students, businessmen, laborers, soldiers, and others

798
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,440
have no choice but to take direct action",

799
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:51,760
it's not necessary to be so tough.

800
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,480
Shizhi, why is this unnecessary?

801
00:34:54,640 --> 00:34:56,960
This sentence is the most important, it cannot be put aside.

802
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,360
Shizhi, let me explain.

803
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:01,840
From the New Cultural Movement to the May Fourth Movement,

804
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:03,840
this is a causal relationship.

805
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:06,480
The former is ideological enlightenment.

806
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:08,240
The latter is puts it into action.

807
00:35:09,120 --> 00:35:10,320
Whether you like it or not

808
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:12,400
these are the results of the direct promotion

809
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:14,000
of you and me over the years.

810
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:16,240
Now, the nation has awakened

811
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:17,760
and is putting into action.

812
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:19,040
This is a leap.

813
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,240
As the initiator, we can't stop it.

814
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:23,840
You can't stop it.

815
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:26,800
Mr. Sun Yat-sen said

816
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,360
the world trend is mighty and irreversible.

817
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:32,400
Follow it, and you will prosper; defy it, and you will die.

818
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,560
We should be promoters

819
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,160
not capitulators.

820
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,160
The only way to save China

821
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,600
is to let the people face it directly.

822
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:43,520
There is no other way.

823
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:47,120
I suppose

